      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Competitive. I'LL KEEP HALF (7) resumed and was too good for a Maiden field over 1300m at York. Is lightly raced and has plenty of scope for improvement. The gun metro hoop is booked and that's a decent push for her chances. SUNBRONZED (2) ran a better race in much tougher over 1200m at Pinjarra Scarpside. Placed at Ascot earlier in the year. This is a lot easier than what he's been facing, and he will be hard to beat. APPARATUS (3) was beaten 2.75 lengths at Pinjarra last time and has one blip in a string of good efforts. Well placed to feature. WHO SAZ YES (9) resumes off much stronger at Ascot and has won fresh. Needs a good ride but also has winning claims. HEZAZEB (4) resumes and might be the best of the rest.",
